pageTitle: Genworth Stats Pack - Round 2 Review - European Tour
textBeforeTable: Ernie Els converted six birdies against one bogey and one double bogey on his way to a second round 69, to lead by one at the half way stage. Looking at his Genworth Statistics, the 43 year old South African and 27 time European Tour winner ranks 1st for Greens in Regulation and 5th for Par 5’s in 2 (his approach play has been the foundation of his great scoring so far). We should also draw attention to Ernie’s incredible Par 5 Scoring average of 3.88. Ernie ELS -12 Round 2 of the BMW International Open produced 78 sub-par rounds and a field average score of 71.81. Ernie Els leads on -12 with Baldwin, Levy, Willett and Wiesberger following behind.
